column5: We have been in the ice box for a while now. Earliest I've ever needed to put on the extension. Nonetheless I've been putting the new rig through the paces and catching a few good fish.  Hope everyone has a safe, lucky and slightly warmer 2014 on the ice.
Wow…Awesome rig….awesome fish….crazy being out in this
Dang dood!  Dunno if I like the ride or the eye more.  Good to hear from ya Jay.  See that fishing Fishin' God's Country is treating ya well.
wow !!! awesome ride jason,and tanker eye too !!!! tight-lines
Who said good gears don't make you a better fisherman!!  Nice hawgeye dude.
Prepare for it and its great. Keeps the masses off the lakes and leaves lots of room to roam. Good gear, survival kit, spare parts and you can have a blast.
Dude you look like phil kessel
Winnipeg...the only place in the world that when the wind stops blowing, someone falls over.
Awwww Crap.  Thanks for making me miss my Rhino even more  Awesome reward for your efforts.
